Reference-contexts: It was used with Fortran90 to parallelize a well-known and widely used regional weather model, the Penn State/NCAR Mesoscale Model MM5 [1]. It is similar to efforts of a number of other groups: Comlib <ref> [2] </ref>, LPARX [3], and NNT/SMS [5] in that it provides high-level, efficient mechanisms for performing data parallel computations over multiple interelated grids. Like the LAPRX software abstractions, RSL is able to support dynamic load balancing, efficient inter-grid communication, irregularly shaped logical domains and irregularly shaped processor sub-domains.
